WEBVTT

00:02.792 --> 00:04.661
Here's a little wisdom
from Grandpa ‐‐

00:04.661 --> 00:07.775
the morning is the one part
of the day you can control

00:07.775 --> 00:10.341
before you're buried
under the crap avalanche.

00:10.341 --> 00:14.589
So, you get your paper ready,
make some eggs,

00:14.589 --> 00:18.092
a mess of bacon,
grab a handful of heart pills

00:18.092 --> 00:21.512
so you've got a shot at doing
the whole thing again tomorrow.

00:21.512 --> 00:25.016
Now, watch and learn.

00:25.016 --> 00:26.059
Morning, Grandpa.

00:26.059 --> 00:27.769
Morning, bud.

00:27.769 --> 00:29.479
Here's a piece
of real bacon

00:29.479 --> 00:31.856
before Captain Darlene of
the vegan police gets here.

00:35.360 --> 00:36.152
[ Mug thuds ]

00:38.363 --> 00:40.156
[ Coffee pours ]

00:40.156 --> 00:44.077
I have so little
in my life.

00:44.077 --> 00:45.954
What have you done
to my newspaper?

00:45.954 --> 00:47.455
I have a school
assignment.

00:47.455 --> 00:51.209
I have to find an article
about business and finance,

00:51.209 --> 00:54.003
but not in the "Business
and Finance" section.

00:54.003 --> 00:56.047
I don't know the right way
to <i>open</i> one of these.

00:56.047 --> 00:57.590
Eh, eh, eh.

00:57.590 --> 00:59.050
Here, here, here.

00:59.050 --> 01:01.386
I'll give you
the "Entertainment" section.

01:01.386 --> 01:04.472
I'm sure there's something
about money in there.

01:04.472 --> 01:07.058
Probably the government
giving my tax dollars

01:07.058 --> 01:09.936
to some ballet company
who's gonna cure climate change

01:09.936 --> 01:11.771
through
interpretive dance.

01:14.190 --> 01:15.984
[ Pages rustle ]

01:20.780 --> 01:22.031
Oh, found one!

01:22.031 --> 01:23.992
Wow!

01:23.992 --> 01:27.287
Did you know that there are
more millionaires now

01:27.287 --> 01:29.080
than ever before?

01:29.080 --> 01:31.541
No, by the time I got to
that part in the paper,

01:31.541 --> 01:34.043
there was a hole in it.

01:34.043 --> 01:36.087
Morning.
There's your mother.

01:36.087 --> 01:37.422
Go cut up
something <i>she</i> loves.

01:37.422 --> 01:39.882
I found my business article
for school.

01:39.882 --> 01:41.467
There's more millionaires
than ever.

01:41.467 --> 01:43.845
Oh, and if you apply yourself,
you can be one, too.

01:43.845 --> 01:44.887
Really?

01:44.887 --> 01:46.180
No,
those days are over.

01:48.057 --> 01:50.685
How long is Bev
gonna be staying with us?

01:50.685 --> 01:52.770
Well, when Jackie
threw her out,

01:52.770 --> 01:55.940
she said she never wanted
to speak to her again.

01:55.940 --> 02:00.778
Did you know your grandmother
now bathes with the door open

02:00.778 --> 02:03.364
because she's worried
about falling?

02:03.364 --> 02:04.449
I'm worried
about seeing it

02:04.449 --> 02:06.784
and throwing myself
down the stairs.

02:06.784 --> 02:08.411
Uh, not necessary.

02:08.411 --> 02:11.956
If you actually see that,
you'll instantly turn to salt.

02:11.956 --> 02:14.375
Why exactly did Jackie
kick her out?

02:14.375 --> 02:17.337
She's pissed because Grandma
gave me power of attorney.

02:17.337 --> 02:19.297
Power of attorney.

02:19.297 --> 02:22.091
Does that mean you have
the power to pull the plug?

02:22.091 --> 02:23.343
Yes.

02:23.343 --> 02:24.719
Even if she's
sick or not?

02:24.719 --> 02:27.013
No.

02:27.013 --> 02:29.974
I'm also managing her assets,
including the old Lunch Box.

02:29.974 --> 02:31.601
Bev said
she got rid of that.

02:31.601 --> 02:32.977
Hold on to your hat...

02:32.977 --> 02:34.979
She lied.

02:34.979 --> 02:36.981
Jackie and Becky
want to reopen it,

02:36.981 --> 02:39.817
and they're mad at me for saying
I had to think about it.

02:39.817 --> 02:41.986
I've been around
a little bit.

02:41.986 --> 02:43.237
Want a piece
of advice?

02:43.237 --> 02:44.447
Sure.

02:44.447 --> 02:47.492
Give everything to Jackie,
throw Bev in a well.

02:47.492 --> 02:49.202
I wish it was that simple.

02:49.202 --> 02:51.913
But Grandma Bev wants
to leave money for everyone.

02:51.913 --> 02:54.082
And it's a big risk
renting to them.

02:54.082 --> 02:55.583
If she's got
so much money,

02:55.583 --> 02:57.085
why the hell is she
staying here?

02:57.085 --> 02:59.754
Well, she's old, and she
wants to be around family.

02:59.754 --> 03:01.381
She says she feels
comfortable here.

03:01.381 --> 03:02.673
Who made her
feel comfortable?

03:02.673 --> 03:03.758
I want a name.

03:09.555 --> 03:17.355
♪♪

03:17.355 --> 03:25.196
♪♪

03:25.196 --> 03:33.204
♪♪

03:33.204 --> 03:40.753
♪♪

03:44.006 --> 03:46.092
<i>"The Conners" is filmed</i>

03:46.092 --> 03:46.843
<i>in front of</i>
<i>a live studio audience.</i>

03:46.843 --> 03:48.094
Jackie: Hey.
Hey, Jackie.

03:48.094 --> 03:50.263
I've got a plan to help us
get the Lunch Box.

03:50.263 --> 03:51.556
So do I.

03:51.556 --> 03:52.890
I get a lawyer,
we establish that

03:52.890 --> 03:54.725
Bev was not
of sound mind

03:54.725 --> 03:57.186
when she gave Darlene
power of attorney.

03:57.186 --> 03:59.313
How can you prove that?

03:59.313 --> 04:01.399
Oh, for God sakes,
we just let the woman talk.

04:02.942 --> 04:05.945
I agree an all‐out war
is a good opening move,

04:05.945 --> 04:08.865
and obviously
a lot of fun for you.

04:08.865 --> 04:10.783
But we have to
prove to Darlene

04:10.783 --> 04:12.994
that our restaurant's
a good idea

04:12.994 --> 04:14.620
and we can
make it work.

04:14.620 --> 04:16.581
[ Exhales deeply ]

04:16.581 --> 04:19.667
Well, I was looking forward
to crushing Bev in court

04:19.667 --> 04:21.002
and having her committed,

04:21.002 --> 04:23.504
but I'm intrigued
by the binder.

04:23.504 --> 04:24.964
Go on.

04:24.964 --> 04:27.967
We need to present Darlene
with a business plan.

04:27.967 --> 04:31.888
Our overall concept,
our target market, our menu.

04:31.888 --> 04:33.890
What do all the struggling
people in this town need?

04:33.890 --> 04:35.892
Healthcare?
Jobs? Hope?

04:37.560 --> 04:40.188
And what do you need when you're
not getting any of those things?

04:40.188 --> 04:42.982
Alcohol? Drugs?
Dog races?

04:42.982 --> 04:45.526
And comfort food!

04:45.526 --> 04:47.653
Comfort.

04:47.653 --> 04:51.782
Who doesn't
want comfort?

04:51.782 --> 04:53.409
Welcome to
the new Lunch Box!

04:53.409 --> 04:54.368
[ Gasps ]

04:54.368 --> 04:56.454
May I recommend
our specialty?

04:56.454 --> 04:59.582
It's delicious, filling,
and you can only get it here.

04:59.582 --> 05:01.542
Yes, please.
What is it?

05:01.542 --> 05:03.961
No idea.

05:03.961 --> 05:05.505
What's your favorite
comfort food?

05:05.505 --> 05:07.381
Uh, well, I don't know.

05:07.381 --> 05:08.508
Uh, I like
something hearty.

05:08.508 --> 05:10.843
Like chili or stew

05:10.843 --> 05:12.428
with a big piece of bread
to soak it up.

05:12.428 --> 05:15.223
I love that!
And it's cheap to make.

05:15.223 --> 05:17.975
Stew is basically
leftovers.
Yeah.

05:17.975 --> 05:23.147
And day‐old bread springs back
to life in a broth!

05:23.147 --> 05:27.902
We could do beef stew,
lamb stew, vegetarian stew.

05:27.902 --> 05:29.153
And here's the thing,

05:29.153 --> 05:30.488
if I wanted stew
right now,

05:30.488 --> 05:31.239
I wouldn't know
where to go.

05:31.239 --> 05:32.573
Exactly!

05:32.573 --> 05:33.991
That's why
we should call it

05:33.991 --> 05:35.743
"The Place You Go
To Get Stew"!

05:35.743 --> 05:38.037
Mmm.
Too long.

05:38.037 --> 05:40.248
It needs to be
quick and punchy.

05:40.248 --> 05:41.916
How about, uh...

05:41.916 --> 05:43.876
"It Takes Stew To Tango"?

05:43.876 --> 05:45.628
Yeah, yeah.

05:45.628 --> 05:48.756
Or "What's Stew, Pussycat?"

05:50.258 --> 05:53.636
We probably shouldn't use "stew"
and "cat" in the same name.

05:53.636 --> 05:54.887
Yeah, got it, got it.

05:54.887 --> 05:57.223
"I Get A Kick
Out of Stew."

05:57.223 --> 05:58.975
"Here's Looking at Stew,
Kid."

05:58.975 --> 06:01.143
"You, Me,
and a Dog Named Stew."

06:01.143 --> 06:02.687
Oh, no,
that's the cat problem.

06:02.687 --> 06:04.605
Yeah. Yeah. Wow.

06:04.605 --> 06:07.066
♪♪

06:07.066 --> 06:09.610
I'm going down to
the truck dealership.

06:09.610 --> 06:12.780
They got a thing where you get
a free turkey with a test drive.

06:12.780 --> 06:14.699
The trick is getting
that bird out of there

06:14.699 --> 06:15.783
before they run
my credit.

06:17.243 --> 06:18.494
Okay.

06:18.494 --> 06:19.537
Do you like what I did

06:19.537 --> 06:21.831
with the Thanksgiving
place settings?

06:21.831 --> 06:24.667
Let's just say
I do.

06:24.667 --> 06:26.460
What would I
be noticing?

06:26.460 --> 06:28.337
They're all personalized.

06:28.337 --> 06:32.258
Yours has the reflection
of the TV in its eyes,

06:32.258 --> 06:35.970
and he's gonna be holding
a little beer.

06:35.970 --> 06:38.598
Like you looked into
my very soul.

06:38.598 --> 06:40.725
Thanks.

06:40.725 --> 06:43.853
I'm gonna put name tags on them,
but I need to know who's coming.

06:43.853 --> 06:45.563
The usual suspects.

06:45.563 --> 06:47.231
Even though Aunt Jackie
and Aunt Becky

06:47.231 --> 06:48.524
are fighting
with my mom?

06:48.524 --> 06:49.859
They'll work it out.

06:49.859 --> 06:51.277
Families fight
all the time.

06:51.277 --> 06:53.779
But they <i>always</i> come together
for the holidays

06:53.779 --> 06:54.780
so they can fight
in person.

06:56.449 --> 06:58.200
Hey, Grandpa.

06:58.200 --> 07:00.494
Can Odessa come over
for Thanksgiving?

07:00.494 --> 07:03.331
There's gotta be
somebody else.

07:03.331 --> 07:04.457
Please?

07:04.457 --> 07:06.167
Her family's not
gonna be around.

07:06.167 --> 07:08.669
Well...

07:08.669 --> 07:11.964
I guess we looked weird
to the Indians, so sure.

07:11.964 --> 07:13.966
Grandpa,
they're Native Americans.

07:13.966 --> 07:15.301
Don't worry, son.

07:15.301 --> 07:17.094
Me and my kind
are on our way out.

07:20.723 --> 07:24.018
Each person's place setting
represents them in some way.

07:24.018 --> 07:26.062
Tell me something about you
that I can use.

07:26.062 --> 07:28.814
Oh, I don't want to be trapped
by the details of my life.

07:31.359 --> 07:33.569
Okay, I'll just make
a generic turkey

07:33.569 --> 07:35.654
with Doc Martens
and a bad attitude.

07:38.157 --> 07:41.035
I want my turkey wearing
a black hood and carrying an axe

07:41.035 --> 07:43.579
so, ironically, <i>he</i> is
the executioner for once.

07:43.579 --> 07:46.248
Sorry. You and Mom
can't have the same thing.

07:47.917 --> 07:50.795
Hey, Mark, put this stuff in
the fridge in the garage, okay?

07:50.795 --> 07:52.380
Thank you.

07:52.380 --> 07:54.256
So, how are you doing,
Odessa?

07:54.256 --> 07:56.050
Ugh!

07:56.050 --> 07:59.345
Why are you always prying
into my friends' lives?

07:59.345 --> 08:00.721
I'm sorry.

08:00.721 --> 08:02.348
I must have used
the wrong words.

08:02.348 --> 08:05.851
What I meant to say was,
"So, how are you doing, Odessa?"

08:05.851 --> 08:07.853
You don't really care,
right?

08:07.853 --> 08:09.605
Not really.
Just being polite.

08:09.605 --> 08:10.564
So I don't
have to answer?

08:10.564 --> 08:11.607
Nope.

08:11.607 --> 08:12.900
‐Good.
‐Good.

08:15.861 --> 08:17.696
Uh‐oh.
Don't worry.

08:17.696 --> 08:18.906
We're not here
to fight.

08:18.906 --> 08:21.826
We just came to ask you,
when was the last time

08:21.826 --> 08:25.621
you had a bowl
of delicious stew?

08:29.208 --> 08:30.584
Um...

08:33.963 --> 08:36.257
I ‐‐ I ‐‐ I'm gonna say
two years.

08:36.257 --> 08:39.009
But I really have
to check my records.

08:39.009 --> 08:42.638
We have a perfect idea
for the Lunch Box.

08:42.638 --> 08:44.557
Comfort food.

08:44.557 --> 08:46.016
We did
some casual polling

08:46.016 --> 08:49.061
with people in the
HomeTown Buffet parking lot.

08:49.061 --> 08:53.149
We said, "Stew,"
they said, "Where?"

08:53.149 --> 08:56.861
And these people had just
polished off a buffet.

08:56.861 --> 08:59.280
It's all here.

08:59.280 --> 09:01.282
Start‐up costs,

09:01.282 --> 09:03.117
projected
profit‐loss statement,

09:03.117 --> 09:04.285
employee wages.

09:04.285 --> 09:05.745
We want you to know
that we're on

09:05.745 --> 09:08.205
solid economic ground
with this.

09:08.205 --> 09:10.249
And you don't have to rent
to some stranger.

09:10.249 --> 09:12.418
All the money stays
in the family.

09:12.418 --> 09:15.421
Like when Jimmy Dean buys
his own sausage.

09:17.548 --> 09:19.508
[ Mouths "Smart" ]

09:19.508 --> 09:22.136
Wow. I mean, you guys have put
a lot of thought into this.

09:22.136 --> 09:23.220
Thank you.

09:23.220 --> 09:24.764
Here's the thing.
[ Sighs ]

09:24.764 --> 09:28.392
Um,
I got another offer

09:28.392 --> 09:30.478
from a chain called
Doctor Drumstick.

09:30.478 --> 09:32.354
They have franchises
all over the Midwest.

09:32.354 --> 09:33.522
They want
a three‐year lease,

09:33.522 --> 09:35.316
starting paying rent
immediately.

09:35.316 --> 09:38.694
Well, sure,
because he's a doctor.

09:38.694 --> 09:40.821
We don't have
that kind of capital.

09:40.821 --> 09:42.364
[ Sighs ]
We just need a chance.

09:42.364 --> 09:45.284
Somebody gave Doctor Drumstick
a chance!

09:45.284 --> 09:46.452
Before that,
he was just a man

09:46.452 --> 09:48.370
with a malpractice suit
and a dream.

09:48.370 --> 09:50.414
Well, look,
your business plan shows

09:50.414 --> 09:52.458
you can't even pay rent
for the first year.
[ Sighs ]

09:52.458 --> 09:54.084
And even then,
you might not make it.

09:54.084 --> 09:56.170
I'm sorry, you guys,
it's just too big of a gamble.

09:56.170 --> 09:58.798
Oh, I see why
Bev picked you.

09:58.798 --> 10:02.760
You're just like her.
95 pounds of angry gristle.

10:05.679 --> 10:07.807
You think I like
being in this position

10:07.807 --> 10:09.350
of denying you something
that you want?

10:09.350 --> 10:11.185
Actually,
I think you do.

10:13.270 --> 10:14.814
Becky, come on.

10:14.814 --> 10:16.357
I mean,
you understand, right?

10:16.357 --> 10:17.858
Most new restaurants
fail.

10:17.858 --> 10:19.401
You really want to pin
all your hopes on that?

10:19.401 --> 10:21.862
I have to.

10:21.862 --> 10:24.615
I can't wait for Bev to die
and leave me money.

10:24.615 --> 10:26.116
She made a deal
with the Devil,

10:26.116 --> 10:27.868
and he's in no hurry
to live with her.

10:30.871 --> 10:33.332
Okay, then just answer
one question ‐‐

10:33.332 --> 10:35.000
Why do you think
you'll succeed

10:35.000 --> 10:37.086
in a location that's
put three restaurants

10:37.086 --> 10:39.588
and a psychic
out of business?

10:39.588 --> 10:42.258
Hey, if the psychic didn't see
that coming, that's on her.

10:44.760 --> 10:47.304
You just came up with this idea
like a week ago.

10:47.304 --> 10:48.848
Don't make me
the bad guy here.

10:48.848 --> 10:50.766
You are so full of it.

10:50.766 --> 10:51.851
When my life
was falling apart,

10:51.851 --> 10:53.519
you were all,
"I'm here for you.

10:53.519 --> 10:55.062
You can do anything."

10:55.062 --> 10:56.772
But when I have
a shot at something,

10:56.772 --> 10:58.399
you show me
how you really feel.

10:58.399 --> 11:00.192
What are you
talking about?
[ Basket thuds ]

11:00.192 --> 11:02.278
You keep saying you don't
want me to fail.

11:02.278 --> 11:04.154
I think you don't want
me to succeed.

11:04.154 --> 11:05.531
What?

11:05.531 --> 11:06.907
Why would you
think that?

11:06.907 --> 11:09.201
'Cause you just lost
two boyfriends,

11:09.201 --> 11:10.619
you're living at
your parents' house,

11:10.619 --> 11:12.246
and you're
stuck working

11:12.246 --> 11:13.956
at that sleazy
mugshot magazine.
[ Scoffs ]

11:13.956 --> 11:15.833
You're worried
I'm gonna pass you by

11:15.833 --> 11:17.585
and have
a successful life.

11:17.585 --> 11:20.421
Whoa, is that
where we're going?

11:20.421 --> 11:22.172
'Cause I will
take that ride.

11:22.172 --> 11:24.550
You're a forty‐four‐year‐old
waitress living under the house

11:24.550 --> 11:27.011
like an old
Christmas tree.

11:27.011 --> 11:30.681
At least I got out
of my old bedroom.

11:30.681 --> 11:34.184
Uh, I'm in D. J.'s room.

11:34.184 --> 11:37.062
And you know what?
At least I'm above sea level.

11:37.062 --> 11:38.981
Climate change is gonna
melt Greenland,

11:38.981 --> 11:40.482
everything's
gonna flood,

11:40.482 --> 11:42.109
and you're gonna wake up with
a polar bear in your bed.

11:43.861 --> 11:45.905
At least somebody's
in my bed!

11:48.616 --> 11:50.034
It's a bear, Becky!

11:50.034 --> 11:51.160
You're sick!

11:51.160 --> 11:52.953
♪♪

11:56.040 --> 11:58.042
♪♪

11:58.042 --> 12:01.378
I got your text.
What happened to your bike?

12:01.378 --> 12:02.630
That's what
I was wondering.

12:02.630 --> 12:05.215
Last time I saw it,
it was in the garage.

12:05.215 --> 12:07.009
Do either of you
know anything about this?

12:07.009 --> 12:11.096
No.
But it doesn't look right.

12:11.096 --> 12:12.848
The funny thing is,

12:12.848 --> 12:15.225
there's a Doc Marten boot
stuck under it.

12:15.225 --> 12:16.352
Uh‐oh.

12:16.352 --> 12:17.311
You know who
wears those?

12:17.311 --> 12:19.605
The mailman.

12:19.605 --> 12:21.690
It's a woman's size 6.

12:21.690 --> 12:25.361
She's a woman, but she
identifies as a mailman.

12:25.361 --> 12:27.279
A lot of them do.
It's crazy.

12:27.279 --> 12:28.280
We gotta dip.

12:28.280 --> 12:30.658
Freeze.

12:30.658 --> 12:32.576
You guys tried
to ride my bike.

12:32.576 --> 12:34.954
No. We just wanted
to take pictures on it.

12:34.954 --> 12:35.955
The light's better
out here.

12:35.955 --> 12:37.831
[ Sighs ]
The key is in it.

12:37.831 --> 12:39.041
It's hard to push.

12:39.041 --> 12:40.751
It's way heavier
than it looks.

12:40.751 --> 12:43.879
You're in tremendous shape
for a guy your age.

12:43.879 --> 12:46.173
Nobody ever touches
this bike.

12:46.173 --> 12:47.883
Ever.

12:47.883 --> 12:51.178
Odessa, you're not allowed
over here anymore.

12:51.178 --> 12:52.680
Respect.

12:54.223 --> 12:55.349
Grandpa!

12:55.349 --> 12:56.433
Come on.
You can't do that.

12:56.433 --> 12:57.851
She's my friend.

12:57.851 --> 13:01.522
Yes, I can.
My bike, my house, my rules.

13:01.522 --> 13:03.565
And you're gonna pay for
that broken mirror.

13:03.565 --> 13:06.151
You know, I thought you were
so much cooler than this.

13:06.151 --> 13:08.612
We were gonna hashtag the photo
"Grandpa rides hard,"

13:08.612 --> 13:09.697
but now you've blown it.

13:11.365 --> 13:13.200
Actually, don't look
that hashtag up.

13:18.372 --> 13:19.957
[ Door closes ]

13:19.957 --> 13:21.834
Just finished
Odessa's place setting.

13:21.834 --> 13:24.628
It took me a while to
really capture her spirit,

13:24.628 --> 13:26.714
but I'm happy
where it ended up.

13:29.174 --> 13:30.342
She's not coming.

13:30.342 --> 13:31.885
Son of a buttercup!

13:34.263 --> 13:35.097
Language.

13:38.392 --> 13:40.144
Hey.

13:40.144 --> 13:42.354
I got a little something
for baby Bev.

13:42.354 --> 13:43.522
[ Chuckles ]

13:43.522 --> 13:44.690
We got to
get her mind right

13:44.690 --> 13:47.484
before the Cheeseheads
get ahold of her.

13:47.484 --> 13:48.861
I hear that.

13:48.861 --> 13:51.447
I won it at the claw machine
at the bowling alley.

13:51.447 --> 13:54.450
Some idiot kid didn't know you
get two chances for your dollar.

13:56.910 --> 13:58.203
Are you packing?

13:58.203 --> 13:59.872
Yeah.

13:59.872 --> 14:01.749
I thought about it,
and I gotta move out.

14:01.749 --> 14:02.833
What?

14:02.833 --> 14:04.918
I'm going to live
with Jackie.

14:04.918 --> 14:08.672
This isn't because of that
stupid restaurant, is it?

14:08.672 --> 14:11.759
Every time I see Darlene,
I get angry,

14:11.759 --> 14:14.052
and I don't want my baby
growing up around that.

14:14.052 --> 14:15.846
Look, you got to think
this through, Becky.

14:15.846 --> 14:17.222
If you move out,

14:17.222 --> 14:18.515
Bev's gonna move in
down here

14:18.515 --> 14:19.892
and stay until she dies.

14:19.892 --> 14:23.812
And I'm too old to carry her
lifeless body up the stairs.

14:23.812 --> 14:26.106
Cut her up
and make trips.

14:26.106 --> 14:28.275
See?
You can't go.

14:28.275 --> 14:31.487
No one else will make
that joke with me.

14:31.487 --> 14:34.198
Come on. I love having you and
the baby here in the house.

14:34.198 --> 14:36.116
After the worst year
of my life,

14:36.116 --> 14:38.535
you guys made me feel good
about things again.

14:38.535 --> 14:40.078
Don't do this to me.

14:40.078 --> 14:42.206
Hey, I don't wanna
do this, either.

14:44.374 --> 14:46.627
What ‐‐ What do I have to do?
Beg you?

14:46.627 --> 14:48.253
Okay,
I'm begging you.

14:48.253 --> 14:50.005
Dad,
you can come visit.

14:50.005 --> 14:51.465
It's not the same.

14:51.465 --> 14:53.550
We have breakfast
together.

14:53.550 --> 14:56.553
I give her my wisdom,
she smiles and poops.

14:56.553 --> 14:58.263
We have a routine.

14:58.263 --> 15:01.266
Well, you could've changed her
every once in a while

15:01.266 --> 15:02.518
instead of
handing her to me.

15:02.518 --> 15:04.895
That's <i>our</i> routine.

15:04.895 --> 15:06.188
I love you, Dad.

15:06.188 --> 15:08.148
But I have
to finish packing.

15:08.148 --> 15:09.942
Could you grab my other suitcase
out of the garage?

15:09.942 --> 15:13.195
I'm sorry,
I won't help you leave.

15:13.195 --> 15:16.615
♪♪

15:19.201 --> 15:20.993
[ Knock on door ]

15:20.993 --> 15:23.621
Darlene: Put away your Bible,
we have to talk.

15:23.621 --> 15:26.999
Did you get my text
about Grandpa?

15:26.999 --> 15:28.042
Yes, I did.

15:28.042 --> 15:29.794
He banned Odessa.

15:29.794 --> 15:31.087
You gotta tell him
he can't do that.

15:31.087 --> 15:32.213
He's not my father.

15:32.213 --> 15:33.172
[ Scoffs ]

15:33.172 --> 15:34.716
Well, we are living
in his house.

15:34.716 --> 15:36.801
Yes, but we pay rent.

15:36.801 --> 15:38.219
Tell him your children
should have the right

15:38.219 --> 15:39.804
to bring over
whoever they want.

15:39.804 --> 15:40.805
I can help you
write the text.

15:40.805 --> 15:43.099
No, I‐I got this.

15:43.099 --> 15:45.393
I know exactly
what to say.

15:45.393 --> 15:48.229
"Dad, I agree with you
one hundred percent.

15:48.229 --> 15:50.523
Odessa shouldn't
come over here anymore.

15:50.523 --> 15:52.942
And please don't respond
with the camel emoji again.

15:52.942 --> 15:54.777
It's weird, and nobody
knows what I means."

15:56.362 --> 15:57.989
You're kidding, right?

15:57.989 --> 15:59.782
I don't want her
in the house, either.

15:59.782 --> 16:02.285
She's my only friend
in this crappy town.

16:02.285 --> 16:04.746
Your stoner friend tried
to take a joy ride

16:04.746 --> 16:05.913
with you on the back.

16:05.913 --> 16:07.749
She knows how to ride
a motorcycle.

16:07.749 --> 16:10.418
She got it nine feet
and dropped it on her shoe.

16:10.418 --> 16:13.421
Yeah, okay,
so she apologized.

16:13.421 --> 16:15.214
What's the big deal?

16:15.214 --> 16:16.799
Harris,
the friends you pick

16:16.799 --> 16:18.843
help determine the direction
of your life.

16:18.843 --> 16:20.261
You have to think harder

16:20.261 --> 16:22.138
about who you're gonna
hang around with.

16:22.138 --> 16:24.724
So what are you saying?
I can't pick my own friends now?

16:24.724 --> 16:27.018
Well, you're not
very good at it.

16:27.018 --> 16:29.061
I mean,
you ‐‐ your friend

16:29.061 --> 16:30.229
could've gotten you
killed today.

16:30.229 --> 16:31.355
Do you understand that?

16:32.482 --> 16:34.692
Do you?

16:34.692 --> 16:37.653
Yeah, okay.
I understand that.

16:37.653 --> 16:38.905
[ Scoffs ]

16:38.905 --> 16:40.740
You don't know
how hard it is.

16:40.740 --> 16:42.617
I'm really lonely here.

16:42.617 --> 16:44.285
I just want to
go home to Chicago.

16:44.285 --> 16:46.078
Oh...

16:46.078 --> 16:48.122
I know.
I know.

16:48.122 --> 16:49.415
I'm sorry.

16:51.876 --> 16:53.753
I won't hang out
with Odessa anymore.

16:53.753 --> 16:55.713
Okay? Happy?

16:55.713 --> 16:57.006
Well, I'm happy
you didn't get hurt.

17:05.932 --> 17:08.893
<i>Whoa, she totally</i>
<i>bought that.</i>

17:08.893 --> 17:10.186
<i>You're good.</i>

17:10.186 --> 17:12.021
I know.

17:12.021 --> 17:14.398
I could be a psychopath
or a CEO or something.

17:14.398 --> 17:18.277
I <i>took one of those tests online</i>
<i>to see if I'm a psychopath.</i>

17:18.277 --> 17:20.780
<i>I'm not.</i>

17:20.780 --> 17:23.407
That's okay.
You still have time.

17:23.407 --> 17:24.575
Let's go do something.

17:24.575 --> 17:26.077
I'll be at your place
in 10 minutes.

17:26.077 --> 17:28.996
<i>Wait.</i>

17:28.996 --> 17:30.540
<i>Oh, yeah. I'm here.</i>
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>

17:31.541 --> 17:35.128
♪♪

17:36.671 --> 17:37.505
Nothin'.

17:37.505 --> 17:39.423
[ Can crinkles ]

17:39.423 --> 17:41.467
Alright.

17:41.467 --> 17:44.053
Well, if you don't
get the job done,

17:44.053 --> 17:46.180
your buddies will have
died in vain.

17:46.180 --> 17:47.181
[ Tab pops ]

17:47.181 --> 17:49.267
[ Knock on door ]

17:49.267 --> 17:50.518
Coming!

17:54.647 --> 17:56.190
Why are
you knocking?

17:56.190 --> 17:58.109
Darlene has made me feel
like I'm not family.

17:59.652 --> 18:02.363
Family comes in.
Guests knock.

18:02.363 --> 18:05.867
You made me get out of a chair
so you could prove a point?

18:05.867 --> 18:09.245
I'm here to pick up
the good daughter.
Aw.

18:09.245 --> 18:12.456
Can't you guys
work something out?

18:12.456 --> 18:15.168
I don't like
what's happening here.

18:15.168 --> 18:16.878
Becky's moving out
with the baby,

18:16.878 --> 18:18.296
everybody hates Darlene,

18:18.296 --> 18:20.798
and Bev is
napping in my bed

18:20.798 --> 18:23.176
because she won't
sleep on the sofa.

18:23.176 --> 18:24.927
"It has bugs."

18:24.927 --> 18:26.929
Well, of course it has bugs!
We eat there!

18:29.599 --> 18:31.350
Oh, well,
if you want to blame somebody,

18:31.350 --> 18:33.519
blame my power‐hungry niece
here,

18:33.519 --> 18:35.855
who has completely forgotten
her cool aunt

18:35.855 --> 18:37.523
who gave her
her first beer

18:37.523 --> 18:39.233
so she wouldn't
go to middle school

18:39.233 --> 18:40.610
as a complete nerd.

18:44.864 --> 18:48.201
You guys are totally
overreacting.

18:48.201 --> 18:50.578
If you don't have
six months' rent

18:50.578 --> 18:53.247
to give to some place,
start smaller.

18:53.247 --> 18:54.248
Get a food truck
or something.

18:54.248 --> 18:55.875
We don't want
a food truck.

18:55.875 --> 18:58.461
We want the Lunch Box.
It means something to us.

18:58.461 --> 18:59.670
It's about family.

18:59.670 --> 19:01.297
Not that you would
understand that.

19:01.297 --> 19:02.506
Come on, Becky!

19:02.506 --> 19:04.050
Let's go
back to my place.

19:04.050 --> 19:05.885
Where dreams live.

19:07.595 --> 19:10.514
Becky, come on.
You don't have to move out.

19:10.514 --> 19:12.433
Say goodbye
to baby Bev.

19:12.433 --> 19:13.893
What?

19:13.893 --> 19:15.102
I'm not gonna see
the baby again?

19:15.102 --> 19:16.771
This is crazy!

19:16.771 --> 19:20.358
She seems to be
fine with it.

19:20.358 --> 19:22.735
Well, then, don't plan on
ever seeing Harris again.

19:22.735 --> 19:24.654
I should've said Mark.
People like Mark.

19:26.572 --> 19:27.949
Becky...

19:27.949 --> 19:29.075
Love you, Dad.

19:30.785 --> 19:33.454
[ Sighs ]

19:33.454 --> 19:34.914
Damn it, Darlene.

19:34.914 --> 19:37.500
I don't care what you say,
I don't care how you do it.

19:37.500 --> 19:38.834
Thanksgiving is
next week.

19:38.834 --> 19:41.879
And I want everybody
around that table.

19:41.879 --> 19:44.006
[ Sighs ] I never
ask you for anything,

19:44.006 --> 19:45.633
but now I'm asking.

19:45.633 --> 19:48.928
Fine. I will do whatever I can
to get them here.

19:48.928 --> 19:50.429
But I'll tell you this
right now,

19:50.429 --> 19:53.724
I will not be bullied into
giving them the restaurant.

19:53.724 --> 19:55.726
And don't you ever give me
your power of attorney!

19:55.726 --> 19:57.103
Obviously, you don't
have anything,

19:57.103 --> 19:58.312
I'm just saying it
to make a point.

20:05.653 --> 20:06.654
Hey.

20:06.654 --> 20:08.572
Here's $40
for your mirror.

20:08.572 --> 20:10.866
Sorry,
it's all I have.

20:10.866 --> 20:12.660
And I promise,
I won't lie to you again.

20:14.287 --> 20:17.039
Well, I'm off
to the library.

20:17.039 --> 20:20.835
♪♪

20:23.671 --> 20:26.549
Hey, guys, could you turn down
the TV for a second?

20:26.549 --> 20:28.342
I'd like to
say something.

20:28.342 --> 20:29.760
Okay, but hurry up.

20:29.760 --> 20:33.180
The guy from "Naked and Afraid"
is being chased by bees.

20:33.180 --> 20:35.725
He reached into a hive
to get honey.

20:35.725 --> 20:38.144
Has the guy never seen
a cartoon?

20:38.144 --> 20:40.771
I just want to say
I think it would be nice

20:40.771 --> 20:42.231
at this year's
Thanksgiving,

20:42.231 --> 20:45.067
if everyone took the time to say
what they were thankful for.

20:45.067 --> 20:46.402
I already wrote mine.

20:46.402 --> 20:50.156
"I'm thankful that
my family is all together

20:50.156 --> 20:52.658
and that we all love
each other,

20:52.658 --> 20:56.662
and, no matter what happens,
we always stick together,

20:56.662 --> 20:58.539
because that's
what Conners do."

21:01.542 --> 21:02.835
Nice!

21:04.920 --> 21:07.423
Passive aggressive
with a hint of guilt.

21:10.301 --> 21:12.803
Pretty impressive
for a 12‐year‐old.

21:12.803 --> 21:14.472
You think they don't learn
from you,

21:14.472 --> 21:15.264
but they watch you.

21:18.100 --> 21:18.851
Uh‐oh.
<i>[ Birds chirping</i>
<i>on television ]</i>

21:18.851 --> 21:19.852
Going into quicksand

21:19.852 --> 21:23.439
is not gonna get rid
of the bees.

21:23.439 --> 21:26.108
Eventually it will.
